OL,4,Cschools as 20% of children don't own
OL,5,Cbooks
OL,7,FThey're calling for the Welsh
OL,8,FGovernment to "develop a national
OL,9,Fstrategy for literacy in Welsh and
OL,10,FEnglish that is informed by research
OL,11,Fand the expertise of those working in
OL,12,Fthe field in Wales and other bilingual
OL,13,Fcountries, and stable, long-term
OL,14,Ffunding to implement it; and to make
OL,15,Flibraries in schools mandatory ` with
OL,16,Fappropriate funding for them to be
OL,17,Fstocked with books that excite and
OL,18,Fengage the children of Wales in both
OL,19,FWelsh and English, and animated by
OL,20,Fwriter visits."
